## Game Description: Graceful Radiant Walrus

Graceful Radiant Walrus is a two-player abstract strategy game. The game is played on a square board of size 5x5. Players take turns placing their walruses on the board. The goal is to create a radiant line of walruses that glow with a gentle light.

## Game Rules

### Equipment

The game is played on a 5x5 square board.

### Start Rules

The game starts with an empty board.

### Play Rules

Players take turns placing their walruses on the board. A player can only place a walrus on an empty square.

### End Rules

The game ends when one player creates a radiant line of 5 walruses in a row, either horizontally, vertically, or diagonally. If the board is full and no player has won, the game is a draw.

## Ludax Implementation

```ludax
(game "Graceful Radiant Walrus"
    (players 2)
    (equipment 
        (board (square 5))
    ) 

    (rules 
        (play
            (repeat (P1 P2)
                (place (destination empty))
            )
        )

        (end 
            (if (line 5) (mover win))
            (if (full_board) (draw))    
        )
    )
)
```

## Adding Radiant Line Constraint

To make the game more interesting, we can add a constraint that a player can only win if they have a radiant line of walruses. We can implement this by introducing a new function `radiant_line` that checks if a player has a radiant line.

```ludax
(game "Graceful Radiant Walrus"
    (players 2)
    (equipment 
        (board (square 5))
    ) 

    (rules 
        (play
            (repeat (P1 P2)
                (place (destination empty))
            )
        )

        (end 
            (if (and (line 5) (radiant_line mover)) (mover win))
            (if (full_board) (draw))    
        )
    )
    (functions
        (function radiant_line
            (lambda (mover)
                (exists
                    (and
                        (line 5)
                        (occupied mover)
                    )
                )
            )
        )
    )
)
```

## Adding Glow Effect

To make the game more visually appealing, we can add a glow effect to the walruses. We can implement this by introducing a new effect `glow` that changes the color of the walrus.

```ludax
(game "Graceful Radiant Walrus"
    (players 2)
    (equipment 
        (board (square 5))
    ) 

    (rules 
        (play
            (repeat (P1 P2)
                (place 
                    (destination empty)
                    (effects 
                        (glow mover)
                    )
                )
            )
        )

        (end 
            (if (and (line 5) (radiant_line mover)) (mover win))
            (if (full_board) (draw))    
        )
    )
    (effects
        (effect glow
            (lambda (mover)
                (set_color mover white)
            )
        )
    )
    (functions
        (function radiant_line
            (lambda (mover)
                (exists
                    (and
                        (line 5)
                        (occupied mover)
                    )
                )
            )
        )
    )
    (rendering
        (color P1 black)
        (color P2 white)
    )
)
```

